The paper deals with the analysis of signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) in a heterogeneous cellular network, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the base-station (BS) arrangement, transmission power, and cell association scheme, which are topics related to communication systems (cs.COMM) and system engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper provides an analytical characterization of the coverage probability, which is a topic related to mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
